 <!-- Applet Parameters -->

 <refentry id="man-applet">
  <refmeta>
   <refentrytitle>regina-applet</refentrytitle>
   <manvolnum>7</manvolnum>
  </refmeta>

  <refnamediv>
   <refname>regina-applet</refname>
   <refpurpose>&regina; &java; applet</refpurpose>
  </refnamediv>

  <refsect1>
   <title>Description</title>
   <para>
    &regina; may be run as a &java; applet.  Because applets suffer from
    restricted filesystem access, &regina; will suffer from
    some loss in functionality.  This will include:
    <itemizedlist>
     <listitem><para>
      No ability to save or load files.
     </para></listitem>
     <listitem><para>
      No &jni; access to the calculation engine.  The user interface
      will have to talk to the calculation engine using &corba;, which
      means you will have to run the &corba; calculation engine as a
      separate server program.  This server should be running on the same
      machine that is hosting the applet web page.  The &corba; naming
      service that is used should also be running on this same machine.
     </para></listitem>
     <listitem><para>
      No reading of configuration files.  The only way to customise
      &regina;'s behaviour will be through the applet parameters
      described below.
     </para></listitem>
    </itemizedlist>
    </para>
    <para>
     The applet itself will need access to the main user interface jar
     (<filename>regina.jar</filename>), the jar for &corba; engine
     access (<filename>regina-corba.jar</filename>) and the &btools; jar
     (generally <filename>btools.jar</filename>).
    </para>
  </refsect1>

  <refsect1>
   <title>Parameters</title>
   <para>The applet parameters that &regina; recognises are as follows.</para>
   <variablelist>
    <varlistentry>
     <term><parameter>Docs</parameter>
      (default = <literal>docs</literal>)</term>
     <listitem>
      <para>
       The URL of the directory in which the unpacked documentation
       can be found by the web browser.  This should be the directory
       containing <filename>welcome.html</filename> and the like.
       This URL may be relative to the location of the applet's web page.
      </para>
     </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
    <varlistentry>
     <term><parameter>Engine</parameter>
      (default = <literal>corba</literal>)</term>
     <listitem>
      <para>
       Specifies how the C++ calculation engine will be accessed.
       Recognised values are:
       <variablelist>
        <varlistentry>
         <term><literal>corba</literal></term>
         <listitem><para>
          The engine will be accessed as a &corba; server application,
          possibly running on a different machine.
         </para></listitem>
        </varlistentry>
       </variablelist>
      </para>
     </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
    <varlistentry>
     <term><parameter>Interface</parameter>
      (default = <literal>gui</literal>)</term>
     <listitem>
      <para>
       Specifies which style of interface to use when running
       &regina;.  Recognised values are:
       <variablelist>
        <varlistentry>
         <term><literal>gui</literal></term>
         <listitem><para>
          Run the full &regina; GUI.
         </para></listitem>
        </varlistentry>
       </variablelist>
      </para>
     </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
    <varlistentry>
     <term><parameter>ORBInitialHost</parameter>
      (default = <literal>localhost</literal>)</term>
     <listitem>
      <para>
       The machine on which the &corba; naming service is running.
       Parameter <parameter>org.omg.CORBA.ORBInitialHost</parameter>
       will override this parameter if it is present.
      </para>
     </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
    <varlistentry>
     <term><parameter>ORBInitialPort</parameter>
      (default = <literal>8088</literal>)</term>
     <listitem>
      <para>
       The port on which the &corba; naming service is listening.
       Parameter <parameter>org.omg.CORBA.ORBInitialPort</parameter>
       will override this parameter if it is present.
      </para>
     </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
   </variablelist>
  </refsect1>

